description: Holiday shopping takes a turn for the worse when the Gods choose the Cherry Hill Mall as their battleground. The evil Minog wants Barock’s head on a slab and he’s willing to kill any mall rat that gets in the way. Unfortunately for Zoe, the mall is also the location of her most recent break-up. And now she’s caught in Minog’s cross-hairs. With Barock’s power failing miserably, will he be able to muster the strength to save himself and Zoe from certain death?
name: Issue #2

description: Michael and Sultan Ameer were once friends. So why are they now so hostile? The answer lies in the city of Waters Meet. Ten years ago, Ameer's machine caravan rolled into town--and Michael found himself at the centre of a whirlwind of love, lust, tragedy, and betrayal! Don't miss this special double-length, full-color anniversary issue!
name: Planet Caravan

description:
When the U.S.S. Voyager is crippled and trapped in a veritable Saragasso Sea of space, the crew find themselves threatened by a mysterious and deadly force, and robbed by a similarly stranded Borg ship. His options limited, Tuvok, U.S.S. Voyager's Security Officer, sends a hand-picked Hazard Team to the Borg cube to reclaim the ship's stolen property.

The Hazard Team is Voyager's equivalent of a SEAL or SWAT team - the toughest and bravest from a shipful of the strong and the brave. But an excursion to the stranded Borg cube is just the first of many trials that will eventually pit them against an incredibly powerful enemy, The Forge, and The Forge's homegrown army of killers.

Based on material from the new Activision/Raven Software computer game, STAR TREK: VOYAGER - ELITE FORCE introduces a new crew of commandos who learn that sometimes winning a battle requires teaming with unexpected allies - and that the price of victory may be higher than they want to pay!

Najika heads to Paris for a major cooking competition, while things with Daichi fall apart and personal tragedy strikes again. Will Seiya pick up the pieces? And will Najika stay true to Daichi?

Chapter Titles

  • Recipe 44: Najike and Salt Caramel
  • Recipe 45: Najika and Paella
  • Recipe 46: Najika and the Cocktail
  • Final Recipe: Najika and Crème Brûlée
  • Special Recipe: Akane and Black Sesame Pudding
  • Kitchen Princess Special
name: Happily Ever After?

description: The Wheel of Time turns and Ages come and go, leaving memories that become legend. Legend fades to myth, and even myth is long forgotten when the Age that gave it birth returns again. In the Third Age, an Age of Prophecy, the World and Time themselves hang in the balance. What was, what will be, and what is, may yet fall under the Shadow. Strangers have come to the village of Emond's Field, located in Two Rivers, during the Bel Tine holiday. With theses strangers come stories of the outside world: tales of war and of a man who claims to be the Dragon Reborn, the one prophesized to save the world, and also to destroy it in his madness. For it is known that no man can channel the One Power without going horribly insane!

volume.name: Robert Jordan's The Wheel of Time: Eye of the World

description:
The Silver Surfer is soaring through space when he hears someone calling for help. He discovers a pod located in a star and retrieves it. He releases the woman whose name is Sympira. She claims to be a scientist who was left behind when her sun went nova. She knows the location of their evacuation. They head out together to find it.

Along the way they tell tales of perils to each other and the Surfer speaks of Alicia Masters back on Earth. They arrive to the planet, where the people are well aware of the legend of Sympira. She begins to attack the populous and the truth is revealed. She was responisible for her star exploding and she plans to rule over her people once more on her quest for power.

She tries to stop the Surfer but he will not allow such tyranny to take place. He uses his power to remove all of her power and leaves her normal once again. She does not wish to be left on the planet, but the Surfer tells her she must pay for her crimes.
name: Suddenly ... Sympira!

description: Tai and Agumon crash into a mysterious snow covered land. Just when they begin to think they are alone on the island, they run into an angry Frigimon (a snowman-like digimon). After evading the continuous attacks Agumon finally removes the Black gear from Frigimon's back. Frigimon informs Tai and Agumon that he saw Matt and Gabumon landing in a nearby island,and sortly after he helps them traverse the freezing water and reach the island.On the other side,Matt searchs for his brother in the middle of a snowstorm,only to faint unconscious. Gabumon saves him,and the next day they find again Tai and Agumon.  The boys quarrel for one more time, until they come across a Mojyamon,a furry digimon attacking with his boomerang! Agumon and Gabumon digivolve to save the day. Now,the island starts moving towards the file island and many dangers await!
name: Subzero Ice Punch!
The Rise of the Pillager Queen

name: The Island Came True

description:
Najika is a great cook and likes to make meals for the people she loves. But something is missing from her life. When she was a child, she met a boy who touched her heart - and now Najika is determined to find him. The only clue she has is a silver spoon that leads her to the prestigious Seika Academy.

Attending Seika will be a challenge. Every kid at the school has a special talent, and the girls in Najika's class think she doesn't deserve to be there. But Sora and Daichi, two popular brothers who barely speak to each other, recognize Najika's cooking for what it is: magical. Is either boy Najika's mysterious prince?

Chapter Titles

  • Recipe 1: Najika and Flan
  • Recipe 2: Najika and Taramasalata
  • Recipe 3: Najika and Rainbow Jelly
  • Recipe 4: Najika and Christmas Cookies
  • Recipe 5: Najika and Onion Gratin Soup
name: Hungry Heart

description:
Najika has a special gift. She's a marvelous cook whose food awakens people's fondest memories and feelings of affection. Now she's attending the prestigious Seika Academy, where she hopes to find her "prince," the boy who saved her when she was a little girl. One big problem: it seems that nobody wants her at the college--except two cute brothers, Sora and Daichi, who befriend her right away.

But the super-popular teen model Akane will do anything to drive Najika out of the school, even if it means staging a cooking contest with an award-winning chef as Najika's opponent. Will Najika's magical food warm Akane's cold heart?

Chapter Titles

  • Recipe 6: Najika and Chocolate Macaroons
  • Recipe 7: Najika and Strawberry Shortcake
  • Recipe 8: Najika and the Cake of Rice
  • Recipe 9: Najika and Yogurt Mousse
  • Recipe 10: Najika and Peach Pie
  • Side Story: After A Busy Day
name: Simmering Rivals

description:
Thanks to a magical talent for cooking, Najika is attending Seika Academy, a top private school, and has a great job at the nearby Fujita Diner. Najika believes that her "prince," the boy who once saved her life, is a fellow student. But when it appears that the diner might close, and jealous classmate Akane hatches a sinister plan to drive Najika out of school, Najika retreats to her childhood home to care for her beloved guardian, who has fallen ill. With so much trouble brewing at the academy, will Najika return to the school or just stay home forever?

Chapter Titles

  • Recipe 11: Najika and Polka Dot Pancakes
  • Recipe 12: Najika and the Rolled Sandwich
  • Recipe 13: Najika and the Banana Cream Puff
  • Recipe 14: Najika and Carrot Cake
  • Recipe 15: Najika and Mont Blanc
name: Home Cooking

description:
Najika came to Seika Academy to find the boy who saved her life. She thinks her “prince” might be either Sora or Daichi--the super-cute brothers who are the most popular boys at school. That is, until one of the brothers warns Najika that her mysterious prince may not be all he seems! Will this revelation put an end to Najika’s lifelong quest?

Chapter Titles

  • Recipe 16: Najika and the Omrice
  • Recipe 17: Najika and the Apple Cake
  • Recipe 18: Najika and the Cocoa Scone
  • Recipe 19: Najika and Fruit Agar
  • Kitchen Princess Special
name: The Prince Revealed?

description:
Najika went to Seika Academy with a dream: to find the boy who saved her life and made her smile when everything else had gone wrong. That boy is Sora, the son of the director of the Academy. Now that Najika has found her prince, she’s very happy. But there’s one major problem: Sora’s brother, Daichi, has fallen for Najika!

Chapter Titles

  • Recipe 20: Najika and the Strawberry Tart
  • Recipe 21: Najika and the Castella
  • Recipe 22: Najika and the Crepes
  • Recipe 23: Najika and Soufflé Ice Cream
  • Kitchen Princess Spring Break ♪ Special
name: Something's Cooking

description:
A new student has arrived at Seika Academy, and he’s supposed to take Najika’s place as spokesperson for the cooking school. Seiya is arrogant and bossy, and he cooks with a precision that is the exact opposite of Najika’s almost magical style. It’s hate at first sight, and there’s a twist: Seiya looks exactly like Najika’s lost love, Sora!

Chapter Titles

  • Recipe 29: Najika and the Fruit Cocktail
  • Recipe 30: Najika and the Madeleines
  • Recipe 31: Najika and the Neapolitan Spaghetti
  • Recipe 32: Najika and the Mille-feuille
  • Recipe 33: Najika and the Cheesecake
name: Spitting Image

description:
Najika finally discovers the true identity of her Flan Prince! But will that change her feelings for Daichi and Seiya? Who will be Najika’s true love? And what terrible secret has Daichi himself just stumbled upon?

Chapter Titles

  • Recipe 39: Najike and Cinnamon Rolls
  • Recipe 40: Najika and Hot Chocolate
  • Recipe 41: Najika and Banana Bread
  • Recipe 42: Najika and Chicken Doria
  • Recipe 43: Najika and Vegetable Potage
  • Kitchen Princess Special
name: A Prince Revealed

description: Detonator encounters a turf war between rival superhuman groups in Los Angeles. Dedicated to kill superhumans, he joins the fight. While one group retreats with an abducted rival, the other group convinces Detonator to join them. Detonator is persuaded to join when Stiletto, one of the remaining superhumans, tells Detonator that Messiah, the local crimelord, is the person who killed his wife and daughter.
name: Fear The Hero

description: Is the fatality level at Sunnydale High too much for you? Your local Prom Queen just got pig's blood dumped on her and now might be a good time to transfer? Welcome to Hamilton High, a haven of safety and normalcy, where local brains, jocks, freaks, and geeks mingle with only the usual teen angst. At least, that's what a cheerleader, a jock, a butch enforcer, and the school tramp all thought until they discovered the common terrifying bond and mysterious powers that targeted them as "The Haunted." With powers they don't understand, a mysterious organization out to harness their budding arcane abilities, and their only salvation lying with the creepiest kid in school, these teen lost souls find themselves the only things standing between all manner of occult terror and a student body that could wind up one large dead student body. If you think your high school was bad... think again!
name: The Haunted

description: Rescuing an abducted teammate, Detonator and his allies break into Messiah's headquarter. Detonator confronts Messiah and tells him he is is long lost brother. To stop him, Detonator kills Messiah by detonating him.
name: Reunion

description: What do you do when your every instinct tells you it's time to hit the road and go on the run...but your only vehicle has transmission trouble and nobody's got gas money? If you're the ragtag teens known as The Haunted, you head back to school, challenge your pursuers to take their best shot, and hope your occult and mysterious powers will see you through. But when the spirits of dead students begin manifesting in the school library, The Haunted have to take them out of circulation before some rather stiff late return penalties are invoked! If you think your school was rough, Think Again!
name: Revelations

description:
Najika’s dreams are coming true: She’s in the finals of a national dessert contest and has found her Flan Prince. But then life goes from sweet to sour as she makes a startling discovery–and loses her sense of taste!

Chapter Titles

  • Recipe 24: Najika and the Bruschetta
  • Recipe 25: Najika and the Flan Cake
  • Recipe 26: Najika and the Curry Roll
  • Recipe 27: Najika and the Yogurt Bread
  • Recipe 28: Najika and the Baked Sweet Potato Mash
  • Kitchen Princess Special
name: Recipe For Disaster

description: The forces of The Haunted are split. Half of them are wrestling with demons menacing the library! All this while the mystery of the Gary Cell deepens, an angry ex-boyfriend plots his revenge, Cross's sister wrestles with a drug problem, and Celia tries to decide whether to start sleeping around. Think your high school was rough? Think again!
name: Making A Splash
Zio Paperone e l'insegnamento di Sissa

description:
Najika’s world is falling apart. Lavender House, the orphanage where she grew up, is being shut down, and there’s only one way she can save it. When Najika is challenged to a High Tea cook-off against Seiya, her nemesis, the scheming director of Seika Academy makes Najika an offer: lose the contest on purpose, and he’ll save Lavender House from ruin. Will Najika throw the fight–or will her true self shine through?

Chapter Titles

  • Recipe 34: Najika and the Fruit Jam
  • Recipe 35: Najika and the Tea Sandwich
  • Recipe 36: Najika and High Tea (Part 1)
  • Recipe 37: Najika and High Tea (Part 2)
  • Recipe 38: Najika and Baci
name: High Tea Showdown

description: This is it! The shocking conclusion to Peter David's twisted tale of today's youth is finally here! As Cliff Cross's sister lies on the brink of death, the Gray Cell is planning to put the "scare" in Bomb Scare at Hamilton High. Now, the only member of The Haunted who can possibly head matters off is Stitch... but he's helpless in the clutches of the school nurse! Will they harness their powers together?! Tune in, because if you seriously thought your high school was rough.... think again!
name: Desperate Times
